                <p rend="flushleft">I <hi rend="italic">Report by the Deputies</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council heard and adopted the report of the 122nd meeting of the Deputies
                    submitted by M. Alphand, Acting Chairman.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">II <hi rend="italic">Peace Treaty With Italy: Free Territory of
                        Trieste</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council considered the unagreed sections of the Deputies’ draft text of the
                    principles to be included in the Permanent Statute of the Free Territory (see
                    Annex to Record of 122nd Meeting of Deputies),<note n="65" xml:id="d365fn65">Ante, <ref target="#pg_1321">p. 1321</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">a</hi>) <hi rend="italic">Withdrawal of Troops</hi>
                </p>
                <p>It was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to ask the Military Experts to submit a
                    recommendation on the figures to be inserted in the blank spaces in paragraph
                        (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) of this text.</p>
                <p>It was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to delete the brackets around paragraph (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>).</p>
                <pb facs="1362" n="1338" xml:id="pg_1338"/>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">b</hi>) <hi rend="italic">Appointment of Provisional Council
                        of Government</hi>
                </p>
                <p>It was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to defer a decision on the alternative texts
                    in square brackets until the Deputies had reported on the Permanent Statute as a
                    whole.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">c</hi>) <hi rend="italic">Elections to the Constituent
                        Assembly</hi>
                </p>
                <p>It was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to adopt the whole of this text, the
                    brackets being deleted and the word “technically” substituted for the word
                    “materially” in the third paragraph.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">d</hi>) It was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to adopt the text
                    of the draft protocol concerning the appointment of a governor for Trieste as
                    recommended by the Deputies.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">III <hi rend="italic">Reports of the Committee of Economic
                        Experts</hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">a</hi>) <hi rend="italic">First Report</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Doc</hi>. <gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">
                        <hi rend="italic">CFM</hi>(<hi rend="italic">46</hi>) (<hi rend="italic">NY</hi>)</gloss>
                    <hi rend="italic">17</hi>)<note n="66" xml:id="d365fn66">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1196">p. 1196</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Council <hi rend="italic">adopted</hi> this report and <hi rend="italic">approved</hi> the texts contained in it.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">b</hi>) <hi rend="italic">Second Report</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Doc</hi>. <gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">
                        <hi rend="italic">CFM</hi>(<hi rend="italic">46</hi>) (<hi rend="italic">NY</hi>)</gloss>
                    <hi rend="italic">20</hi>)<note n="67" xml:id="d365fn67">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1227">p. 1227</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>1. <hi rend="italic">Contracts</hi>, (<hi rend="italic">page 3</hi>). The
                        additional paragraph 2(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) proposed by the United
                        Kingdom representative was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi>, as well as the
                        text submitted by the Economic Committee.</item>
                    <label/>
                    <item>In this connection, the special provision relating to the U.S. was <hi rend="italic">agreed.</hi>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Periods of Prescription</hi>. The text submitted for Part
                        II of Annex VII of the Italian Treaty, and for Part II of Annex V of the
                        other treaties was <hi rend="italic">agreed.</hi>
                    </item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Miscellaneous Provisions</hi>. The U.K. delegate withdrew
                        Part IV of Annex VII of the Italian Treaty and Part IV of Annex V of the
                        other treaties.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Claims on Germany</hi> (<hi rend="italic">page 5</hi>).
                        The text proposed by the United States Delegation was approved for inclusion
                        in the Peace Treaties with Italy, Roumania, Bulgaria and Hungary. The first
                        three paragraphs of the United States text were approved for inclusion in
                        the Peace Treaty with Finland.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Insurance</hi> (<hi rend="italic">pages 6 and 7</hi>). The
                        text proposed by the United Kingdom Delegation as set out in paragraph 2 was
                            <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> and that set out in paragraph 5 was
                        adopted with the period of 3 years amended to 18 months.</item>
                    <label>6.</label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Petroleum</hi> (<hi rend="italic">page 8</hi>). The text
                        proposed by the United Kingdom representative to be added to the end of
                        Article 24, paragraph 1, of the Roumanian Treaty was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi>, subject to an amendment by the U.S.S.R. Delegation. The
                        amended text read as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“If necessary the Roumanian Government shall revoke legislation
                                enacted since September 1, 1939, <hi rend="italic">in so far as it
                                    discriminates against</hi> the rights of United Nations
                                nationals.”</p>
                        </quote>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <pb facs="1363" n="1339" xml:id="pg_1339"/>
                <p>In this connection the U.S.S.R. representative proposed the deletion from the
                    Roumanian Treaty of Article 30 bis dealing with the question of fair market
                    prices. After an exchange of views it was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to defer
                    further consideration of the question until later.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">c</hi>) <hi rend="italic">Third Report</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Docs</hi>. <gloss target="#t_CFM1">
                        <hi rend="italic">CFM</hi> (<hi rend="italic">46</hi>)(<hi rend="italic">NY</hi>)</gloss>
                    <hi rend="italic">29 and 30</hi>)<note n="68" xml:id="d365fn68">
                        <gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46) (NY)</gloss>29, November 26, 1946, the
                        Third Report of the Committee of Economic Experts, is not printed. All the
                        amendments and additions to Annex III of the Draft Peace Treaty with Italy
                        that were agreed upon by the Committee and included in its Report were
                        subsequently incorporated in document <gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM (46)
                            (NY)</gloss>30, November 26, 1946, <ref target="#pg_1296">p.
                        1296</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Council proceeded to consider the unagreed sections of these reports on Annex
                    III of the Peace Treaty with Italy and the related provisions of Article 69 with
                    the following results: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Transfer of State and Para-statal Property</hi> (<hi rend="italic">page 2</hi>). The new paragraph 1A recommended by the
                            Committee was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> with the deletion of the
                            brackets round the concluding phrase.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Works of Art, etc., Removed from Ceded Territory</hi>
                                (<hi rend="italic">page 3</hi>). The new paragraph 1C was <hi rend="italic">adopted</hi>, the French Delegation having withdrawn
                            their objections to its inclusion.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Public Debt</hi> (<hi rend="italic">page 4</hi>). The
                            text proposed for paragraph 3 was <hi rend="italic">adopted</hi> with
                            the deletion of all the brackets.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Italian Pension Obligations</hi> (<hi rend="italic">page 5</hi>). The new paragraph 4A recommended by the Committee was
                                <hi rend="italic">adopted</hi> with the deletion of the brackets
                            round the words “or military”.</item>
                        <label>5.</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Concessionary companies</hi> (<hi rend="italic">page
                                5</hi>). This question was <hi rend="italic">reserved</hi> pending
                            final agreement on the problem of reparation.</item>
                        <label>6.</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Property removed from Ceded Territory</hi> (<hi rend="italic">page 7</hi>). The text proposed for the new paragraph
                            10A on this subject was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi>, subject to the
                            words “during the war” being amended to read “after September 3,
                            1943”.</item>
                        <label>7.</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Subparagraph</hi> (<hi rend="italic">g</hi>) <hi rend="italic">of paragraph 5, Article 69</hi> (<hi rend="italic">page 9</hi>). The text proposed for this subparagraph by the French
                            and U.S.S.R. representatives was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi>.<note n="68a" xml:id="d365fn68a">Regarding the report by the Committee of
                                Economic Experts, as included in document <gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM (46) (NY)</gloss>29, see footnote 62,
                                    <ref target="#pg_1332">p. 1332</ref>. The text proposed by the
                                Soviet and French Delegations for this sub-paragraph is included in
                                the United States Delegation Minutes of this meeting of the Council;
                                see <ref target="#pg_1324">p. 1324</ref>.</note>
                        </item>
                        <label>8.</label>
                        <item>The remainder of the text in <gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM (46)
                                (NY)</gloss> 30 was <hi rend="italic">approved.</hi>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">IV <hi rend="italic">Regime of the Danube</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The U.S.S.R. representative submitted the text of a proposal dealing with this
                    question to be recorded as a decision of the Council of Foreign Ministers. The
                    provisional English text read as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Navigation in the Danube shall be free and open on terms of equality in
                            so far as this concerns port and navigation charges and conditions of
                            commercial shipping within the limits of the usual commercial relations,
                            to the nationals, vessels of commerce and goods of all states.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <pb facs="1364" n="1340" xml:id="pg_1340"/>
                <p>It was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to refer this text to the Deputies for
                    drafting and with a view to its eventual inclusion as a Peace Treaty
                    article.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">V <hi rend="italic">Next Meetings of the Council</hi>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <item>Deputies—November 29, 1946, at 11 a.m.</item>
                    <item>Ministers—November 29, 1946, at 4 p.m.</item>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>, November 29, 1946.</item>
                </list>
